# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# This app uses HashRouter (routes are /#/dashboard, not /dashboard), so
# every real in-app navigation already resolves to a single static file
# (index.html) without any server-side help. This rule only matters as a
# safety net for a mistyped/old-style deep link without the #, or any
# other path that isn't an actual file in dist/ — instead of Cloudflare's
# generic 404 page, it serves index.html (which then boots the app
# normally). Cloudflare only applies this when no real static file matches
# the request first, so it never shadows actual assets.
/*  /index.html  200
